  %body
    .content
      %a{ href: "https://github.com/ksylvest/jquery-age"}
        %img.fork{ src: "images/fork.png", alt: "Fork" }
      %h1 jQuery Observe
      %p Observe is a jQuery plugin designed to provide change observation.
      %h2 Example
      %section.example
        %form#search
          %input{ type: 'search', class: 'search', placeholder: "Search" }
        %p Searches:
        #searches
      %h2 Installation
      %p To install download one of these packobserves and include the jquery-observer.js file in your head with the following:
      %section.formats
        .format
          %a.zip{ href: "packages/jquery-observer.zip" }
        .format
          %a.tar{ href: "packages/jquery-observer.tar" }
      %pre
        %code{ data: { languobserve: "html" } }
          = preserve do
            :escaped
              <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.0.2/jquery.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
              <script src="javascript/jquery-observer.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
      %h2 Example
      %p Setting up a date or time is easy. The following snippet is a good start:
      %pre
        %code{ data: { languobserve: "html" } }
          = preserve do
            :escaped
              <form id="search">
                <input type="text" name="search" />
              </form>

              <script type="text/javascript">
                $('#search').observe(function () { alert("observe"); });
              </script>
